Title: The Last Shift
Credit: written by
Author: Filmwright example
Draft date: 2026-07-21
Notes: SC004 — recognition. Target 40s. Plot loose, emotion heavy. POV: Meiling.

INT. CONVENIENCE STORE - NIGHT

Fluorescent hum. Rain beads on the glass. MEILING (50, store apron over a winter coat, hands chapped raw) wipes a counter that is already clean.

A dented floor spring leaves the door ten centimeters open. Cold air nudges a paper bowl on the sill. Steam thins above it.

Outside, tape wrinkles across a notice: 明日六点交接.

KAI (74, coat too thin for the rain, a bag of aluminum cans) fills the doorway. He traces the notice with one finger but does not step in.

MEILING
(not turning)
关东煮在窗边。拿了走吧。

KAI
天亮就交？

MEILING
六点。

She opens the tap. Rinses the cloth. Wrings it once.

KAI
你妈……

The cloth stops between her hands.

MEILING
她去年走的。

The kettle ticks as it cools.

KAI
美玲。

Her thumb presses into a chip on the counter edge. She shuts off the tap.

MEILING
别叫。十二岁以后，我就没爸了。

In the dark cooler door, her reflected eyes lift to Kai. Her shoulders stay square to the sink.

The cloth drops into the basin.

CUT TO:
